    "description": "We at GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd are looking for an experienced Senior Doctor based out of Aurangabad. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nGE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Learning & development budget\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
